LINUX LAB EXERCISE – FILE PERMISSIONS AND UMASK
===============================================

Objective
=========
1. View file and directory permissions.
2. Understand User, Group and Others permissions.
3. Change permissions using Numeric Method.
4. Change permissions using Symbolic Method.
5. Understand and calculate Umask values.

--------------------------------------------------
Exercise 1: Create Lab Environment
--------------------------------------------------

Create a directory and move into it:

# mkdir permission-lab
# cd permission-lab

Create files and directories:

# touch file1 file2
# mkdir dir1 dir2

Verify:

# ls

--------------------------------------------------
Exercise 2: Check Default Permissions
--------------------------------------------------

# ls -l

or

# ll

Observe the output:

-rw-r--r-- 1 root root    0 Jun 18 10:00 file1
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root    6 Jun 18 10:00 dir1

Identify:
-----------
Field 1 : File Type and Permissions
Field 2 : Link Count
Field 3 : Owner
Field 4 : Group
Field 5 : File Size
Field 6 : Last Modified Date and Time
Field 7 : File Name

--------------------------------------------------
Exercise 3: Understanding File Permissions
--------------------------------------------------

Create a file:

# echo "Linux Permission Demo" > file1

Read the file:

# cat file1

Modify the file:

# echo "New Line" >> file1

Provide execute permission:

# chmod +x file1

Check permission:

# ls -l file1

File Permissions:
-----------------
Read (r)    - View file contents
Write (w)   - Modify file contents
Execute (x) - Run script/program

--------------------------------------------------
Exercise 4: Understanding Directory Permissions
--------------------------------------------------

Create files inside directory:

# touch dir1/test1
# touch dir1/test2

List directory contents:

# ls dir1

Create a new file:

# touch dir1/test3

Enter the directory:

# cd dir1
# pwd
# cd ..

Directory Permissions:
----------------------
Read (r)    - List contents
Write (w)   - Create/Delete files
Execute (x) - Enter the directory

--------------------------------------------------
Exercise 5: Numeric Permission Method
--------------------------------------------------

Create a file:

# touch numeric.txt

Assign permission 744:

# chmod 744 numeric.txt

Verify:

# ls -l numeric.txt

Permission Calculation:
-----------------------
7 = rwx = 4+2+1
4 = r--
4 = r--

744 = rwxr--r--

--------------------------------------------------
Exercise 6: Practice Numeric Permissions
--------------------------------------------------

